VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT (?i)(?:--password|--secret|--token|--key|--api-key)\s*=?\s*\S
WHEN EXPR MISSING:\$\{|\$\(
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects credentials passed as command line arguments, which are visible in process listings.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Credentials Passed via Command Line Arguments.
